# rwsdk Router API — Complete Analysis

## 1. Module Entry Point: `rwsdk/router`

**File:** `/home/user/myapp/node_modules/rwsdk/dist/runtime/entries/router.d.ts`

```ts
import "./types/shared";
export * from "../lib/links";
export * from "../lib/router";
export type { DocumentProps, LayoutProps } from "../lib/types";
```

So `rwsdk/router` re-exports everything from `../lib/router` (routes, middleware, etc.) plus `../lib/links` (link helpers) plus `DocumentProps` and `LayoutProps`.

---

## 2. Core Router Types (from `router.d.ts`)

### `RouteMiddleware<T>` — global middleware function signature

```ts
type MaybePromise<T> = T | Promise<T>;

type BivariantRouteHandler<T extends RequestInfo, R> = {
    bivarianceHack(requestInfo: T): R;
}["bivarianceHack"];

export type RouteMiddleware<T extends RequestInfo = RequestInfo> =
    BivariantRouteHandler<T, MaybePromise<React.JSX.Element | Response | void>>;
```

A middleware receives a `RequestInfo` and may return `void` (continue), a `Response` (short-circuit), or a `React.JSX.Element` (render immediately).

### `RouteHandler<T>` — what you pass as the handler argument to `route()`

```ts
type RouteFunction<T extends RequestInfo = RequestInfo> =
    BivariantRouteHandler<T, MaybePromise<Response>>;

type RouteComponent<T extends RequestInfo = RequestInfo> =
    BivariantRouteHandler<T, MaybePromise<React.JSX.Element | Response | void>>;

type RouteHandler<T extends RequestInfo = RequestInfo> =
    | RouteFunction<T>
    | RouteComponent<T>
    | readonly [...RouteMiddleware<T>[], RouteFunction<T> | RouteComponent<T>];
```

A `RouteHandler` can be:
- A single function returning `Response` or JSX
- An array `[middleware1, middleware2, ..., finalHandler]`

### `MethodVerb` — the 6 supported HTTP methods

```ts
declare const METHOD_VERBS: readonly ["delete", "get", "head", "patch", "post", "put"];
export type MethodVerb = (typeof METHOD_VERBS)[number];
// = "delete" | "get" | "head" | "patch" | "post" | "put"
```

### `MethodHandlers<T>` — **the key type for method-aware routes**

```ts
export type MethodHandlers<T extends RequestInfo = RequestInfo> = {
    [K in MethodVerb]?: RouteHandler<T>;
} & {
    config?: {
        disable405?: true;
        disableOptions?: true;
    };
    custom?: {
        [method: string]: RouteHandler<T>;
    };
};
```

