    disable405?: true;
    disableOptions?: true;
}
```

#### `disableOptions: true`

When set, the router **does NOT** automatically handle OPTIONS. Instead, the OPTIONS request falls through to normal method resolution. This means:
- If you defined an `options` handler on the `MethodHandlers` object, it will be used
- If you did NOT define an `options` handler, the router will fall through to 405 handling (or continue to the next route if `disable405` is also set)

